ut also further enhanced the ability of these suburban entities to remain or break away and form independent municipalities. The process was crucial in creating a proliferation of municipalities within metropolitan regions. The book thus shows that the roots of the urban crisis can be found in the interplay between technology, politics, and public works in the American city.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aAnnexation (Municipal government)zUnited StatesxHistory. 0aInfrastructure (Economics)zUnited StatesxHistory. 0aMetropolitan areaszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSuburbszUnited StatesxHistory. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / City Planning & Urban Development.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674272064423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674272064/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK